Six people have been killed and four others seriously injured in a collision between two cars on the Matlala road outside Polokwane in Limpopo. The injured have been taken to hospital. Traffic authorities say it’s believed one of the drivers attempted to overtake in an unsafe place. The road has been closed. Investigations into the cause of the collision are underway. Seven people have died in a head on collision between two sedans outside Polokwane in Limpopo. The driver of a BMW was trying to overtake when he collided with another BMW. #sabcnews pic.twitter.com/l1vQvPnOjL — Katlego Nyoni (@katlego4ever) September 20, 2020 